    {
      "id": "intro-er",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "-ER verbs",
      "body": "# Regular -ER verbs\n\nIn Lesson 6 you learned the **-AR** verbs. Now come the second and third groups: **-ER** and **-IR**. They work almost the same way.\n\nFor an -ER verb, take the stem (the infinitive without -er) and add these endings:\n\n| Subject | Ending | comer (to eat) |\n|---|---|---|\n| yo | -o | **como** |\n| tú | -es | **comes** |\n| él / ella / usted | -e | **come** |\n| nosotros | -emos | **comemos** |\n| vosotros (Spain) | -éis | **coméis** |\n| ellos / ellas / ustedes | -en | **comen** |\n\n**beber** (to drink) works the same way: bebo, bebes, bebe, bebemos, bebéis, beben.\n\nThe accent on **coméis** is mandatory."
    },
    {
      "id": "intro-ir",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "-IR verbs",
      "body": "## Regular -IR verbs\n\nThe -IR verbs use almost the same endings:\n\n| Subject | Ending | vivir (to live) |\n|---|---|---|\n| yo | -o | **vivo** |\n| tú | -es | **vives** |\n| él / ella / usted | -e | **vive** |\n| nosotros | -imos | **vivimos** |\n| vosotros (Spain) | -ís | **vivís** |\n| ellos / ellas / ustedes | -en | **viven** |\n\nThe same pattern applies to **escribir** (to write): escribo, escribes, escribe, escribimos, escribís, escriben — and **abrir** (to open): abro, abres, abre, abrimos, abrís, abren.\n\nThe accent on **vivís** is mandatory."
    },
    {
      "id": "intro-comparison",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "The one difference that matters",
      "body": "## -ER and -IR are almost identical\n\nCompare the two tables closely: in **five of the six** forms the endings are the same (-o, -es, -e, -en). They differ **only** in the **we-form (nosotros)** and the **you-plural form (vosotros)**:\n\n| Subject | -ER (comer) | -IR (vivir) |\n|---|---|---|\n| yo | como | vivo |\n| tú | comes | vives |\n| él / ella | come | vive |\n| **nosotros** | **comemos** | **vivimos** |\n| **vosotros** | **coméis** | **vivís** |\n| ellos / ellas | comen | viven |\n\nJust memorise this one contrast:\n\n- **-ER** → nosotros **-emos**, vosotros **-éis** (comemos, coméis)\n- **-IR** → nosotros **-imos**, vosotros **-ís** (vivimos, vivís)\n\nThe classic beginner mistake is *vivemos* instead of **vivimos**. Everything else is the same. The vosotros form is used mainly in Spain."
    },
